{
  "texts": [
    "The performance of the ensemble in detecting anomalies is evaluated using standard metrics.",
    "Based on the evaluation results, hyperparameters are adjusted, and the ensemble may be retrained to optimize performance.",
    "The final ensemble, E, consisting of multiple base ML models, is now ready for anomaly detection on new and unseen data instances in the WSN.",
    "EFL is integrated into the WSN environment, achieving a collaborative, decentralized, and privacy-preserving approach to anomaly detection, making it more robust, energy-efficient, and adaptable to dynamic environments.",
    "This approach also minimizes the need for data transmission and central processing, which is beneficial for resource-constrained sensor nodes."
  ]
}